<task id="042" project="spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r5">
  <metadata>
    <title>D3-03 Telemetry dashboards (App Insights / Grafana) for R5 Summarize-for-Chat</title>
    <status>not-started</status>
    <estimated-effort>4 hours</estimated-effort>
    <actual-effort></actual-effort>
    <assigned>AI Agent</assigned>
    <started></started>
    <completed></completed>
    <phase>Phase 3 — Polish + Future-Use Validation</phase>
    <wave>P3-2 (parallel-safe with 041; Phase 2 + task 008 are prerequisites)</wave>
    <parallel-safe>true</parallel-safe>
    <dependencies>Phase 2 ✅, task 008 (telemetry events emitted)</dependencies>
    <tags>dashboards, telemetry, kusto, grafana, observability</tags>
    <rigor-level>FULL</rigor-level>
  </metadata>

  <prompt>
    Author the operational dashboards that visualize the R5 Summarize-for-Chat
    telemetry stream emitted by task 008's `R5SummarizeTelemetry`. The dashboards
    are how Operations + the R5 lead answer the four binding observability
    questions from plan.md D3-03 + spec NFR-06 (cost control):

    1. **Invocation counts + path mix** — how often is Summarize-for-Chat invoked,
       and what's the split between the agent-tool path (`path = "agent_tool"`)
       and the direct-endpoint path (`path = "direct_endpoint"`)? Stratified by
       `completion_status`.
    2. **Session-files index size** — distribution of per-session document counts
       observed at `phase ∈ {post_write, post_evict, post_cleanup}` (the
       `r5.session_files.index_size` Histogram from task 008). Drives the
       cleanup-cadence tuning question from spec NFR-02 (assumed 6h cadence; may
       tune to 1h if growth is high).
    3. **Cost-per-session breakdown** — derived from `r5.summarize.total_tokens`
       Histogram + token-pricing constants. Supports capacity planning + the
       budget-burn-down question from spec NFR-06.
    4. **SSE event-rate histogram** — `r5.summarize.latency_ms` distribution +
       Counter rate, both stratified by `path`. Surfaces the FR-02 / NFR-01 SSE
       TTFB &lt; 500ms commitment + identifies regressions.

    The event schema is LOCKED by task 008 (see `notes/task-008-telemetry-evidence.md`
    for the canonical table). This task CONSUMES that schema — Kusto queries
    reference the exact metric names (`r5.summarize.invocation`,
    `r5.summarize.file_count`, `r5.summarize.total_tokens`,
    `r5.summarize.latency_ms`, `r5.session_files.index_size`) and exact dimension
    names (`path`, `completion_status`, `phase`, `tenantId`). A schema breaking
    change downstream would invalidate these dashboards.

    R5 is configuration-first: this task ships dashboard configuration only. It
    does NOT modify BFF code. The R5 publish-size budget (≤ +1 MB across the
    project) is not consumed by this task. Publish-size delta = 0 MB.

    Per CLAUDE.md §10 Placement Justification: dashboards belong in
    `infrastructure/` IaC OR as portal-managed artifacts with re-creation
    documentation in `notes/`. Bicep is preferred (idempotent IaC + reviewable
    diff); portal-managed is acceptable when Bicep authoring cost is
    disproportionate to the value (e.g., exploratory queries during stabilization).
    The placement decision is recorded in task notes.
  </prompt>

  <role>
    Senior observability engineer with deep Azure Monitor / Application Insights
    + Kusto Query Language (KQL) experience, plus working knowledge of Azure
    Dashboard ARM/Bicep authoring (the
    `Microsoft.Portal/dashboards@2020-09-01-preview` resource type used by the
    existing `infrastructure/bicep/modules/dashboard.bicep` precedent). Familiar
    with the OpenTelemetry → App Insights metric / customMetrics ingestion path
    so KQL queries against `customMetrics` / `customEvents` tables target the
    right schema for task 008's emitted instruments.
  </role>

  <goal>
    Four panels are live on a Spaarke Dev dashboard (Bicep-managed preferred,
    portal-managed acceptable with documented re-creation steps), each backed
    by a Kusto query referencing the locked task-008 schema. Each query returns
    real data when run against Spaarke Dev App Insights. The cost-per-session
    panel surfaces the Histogram-driven cost breakdown usable for capacity
    planning. Dashboards are accessible to the R5 lead + Operations via the
    Azure Portal. Placement decision (IaC vs portal-managed) is recorded in
    task notes with rationale. BFF publish-size delta is verified at 0 MB
    (no BFF code change in this task). Quality gates pass.
  </goal>

