  <constraints>
    <constraint source="task 008 — locked schema (BINDING)">Dashboards MUST consume the EXACT metric names + dimension names locked in `notes/task-008-telemetry-evidence.md`: `r5.summarize.invocation` (Counter), `r5.summarize.file_count` (Histogram), `r5.summarize.total_tokens` (Histogram), `r5.summarize.latency_ms` (Histogram), `r5.session_files.index_size` (Histogram). Dimensions: `path` ∈ {`agent_tool`, `direct_endpoint`}, `completion_status` ∈ {`success`, `failed`, `declined`, `cancelled`}, `phase` ∈ {`post_write`, `post_evict`, `post_cleanup`}, optional `tenantId` (low-cardinality). No renames. No schema invention.</constraint>
    <constraint source="R5 CLAUDE.md §3.6 + ADR-029">BFF publish-size verification — this task changes ZERO BFF code; publish-size delta MUST be 0 MB. Document explicitly in task notes that no `dotnet publish` measurement was required because no BFF binary was changed. (Verification is "confirm delta = 0 MB by inspection of changed files.")</constraint>
    <constraint source="R5 CLAUDE.md §3.1 reuse mandate">If Bicep-managed, EXTEND existing `infrastructure/bicep/modules/dashboard.bicep` pattern (mirrors the precedent for AI feature monitoring) rather than introducing a new dashboard authoring pattern. If portal-managed, document the portal-managed rationale + provide a JSON export checked into `infrastructure/dashboards/` so the dashboard is reproducible after tenant rebuilds.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-014">Tenant isolation — if any panel filters or stratifies by `tenantId`, the query MUST scope to a single `tenantId` OR aggregate across tenants without leaking per-tenant identifiers in shared dashboards. Spaarke Dev dashboards may show all tenants; production dashboards (out of scope for R5) would partition per-tenant.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-015">Dashboards / queries MUST NOT surface document content, prompt text, file names, session IDs, correlation IDs, or any other PII from telemetry. Only enums + counts + durations + tenantId. (This is automatic since task 008 already excludes those from dimensions — but verify queries don't reach into other tables that DO carry such fields.)</constraint>
    <constraint source="R5 CLAUDE.md §3.2 + ADR-018">No new feature flags introduced by this task. Dashboards are unconditional artifacts.</constraint>
    <constraint source="spec NFR-06 cost control">Cost-per-session panel MUST derive cost from `r5.summarize.total_tokens` Histogram + the established Azure OpenAI token-pricing constants for the deployed model (record the pricing constants in the dashboard description / annotation so the derivation is auditable and re-runnable when prices change).</constraint>
    <constraint source="spec NFR-02 cleanup cadence tuning">Index-size panel MUST stratify by `phase` so the post-cleanup vs post-write delta is visible — this is the load-bearing chart for the 6h → 1h cadence-tuning decision documented in spec NFR-02 + task 008.</constraint>
    <constraint source="spec FR-02 / NFR-01 SSE TTFB">SSE event-rate / latency panel MUST surface the SSE TTFB &lt; 500ms commitment from FR-02 / NFR-01 — render a p50/p95/p99 line for `r5.summarize.latency_ms` Histogram with a horizontal threshold marker at 500ms so regressions are immediately visible.</constraint>
    <constraint source="path-drift correction (operator note)">Index JSON path is `infrastructure/ai-search/` (NOT `infra/ai-search/`). Verify any path reference in dashboard descriptions / annotations + ensure consistency with existing R5 task POMLs (001 uses `infrastructure/ai-search/`).</constraint>
    <constraint source="project">Each panel MUST be verified against LIVE Spaarke Dev telemetry data — the dashboard ships only when each query returns non-error rows from Spaarke Dev's App Insights instance. If task 008's events have not yet been emitted (because tasks 012/014/015/007 have not yet generated traffic), trigger a synthetic invocation manually to seed data BEFORE marking acceptance complete.</constraint>
    <constraint source="project">Placement decision (Bicep IaC vs portal-managed) MUST be recorded explicitly in task notes with rationale. Bicep is preferred (idempotent + reviewable diff + tenant-rebuild safe); portal-managed is acceptable only when Bicep authoring cost is disproportionate. If portal-managed, include a JSON export in `infrastructure/dashboards/` so the dashboard is reproducible.</constraint>
  </constraints>

