    <patterns>
      <pattern name="Azure Dashboard Bicep pattern" location="infrastructure/bicep/modules/dashboard.bicep">
        The existing `Microsoft.Portal/dashboards@2020-09-01-preview` resource
        pattern + per-tile `MonitorChartPart` / `LogsDashboardPart` parts. Mirror
        this exact structure for the 4 new R5 panels. Parameterize `appInsightsId`
        + `dashboardName` to match precedent. Use `lenses[].parts[]` for layout
        positioning (`x`, `y`, `rowSpan`, `colSpan`).
      </pattern>
      <pattern name="OpenTelemetry → App Insights metric ingestion" location="src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Infrastructure/DI/TelemetryModule.cs">
        OpenTelemetry meters registered via `AddMeter("Sprk.Bff.Api.R5Summarize")`
        export to App Insights via the OTel → AI exporter. Counter measurements
        appear in `customMetrics` table with `name` = meter-prefixed instrument
        name (e.g., `r5.summarize.invocation`). Histogram measurements appear as
        multiple aggregated entries (sum / count / min / max / percentiles
        depending on aggregator config). Dimensions appear in `customDimensions`
        bag. KQL queries `customMetrics | where name == "r5.summarize.invocation"`
        and project `tostring(customDimensions.path)` etc. for stratification.
      </pattern>
      <pattern name="KQL invocation-count query shape" location="(canonical KQL — author this task)">
        ```kusto
        customMetrics
        | where timestamp &gt; ago(24h)
        | where name == "r5.summarize.invocation"
        | extend path = tostring(customDimensions.path),
                 completion_status = tostring(customDimensions.completion_status)
        | summarize count_=sum(valueCount) by bin(timestamp, 5m), path, completion_status
        | render timechart
        ```
        Reference + adapt for the four panels. For cost: multiply
        `r5.summarize.total_tokens` by per-token pricing constant in `extend cost_usd = total_tokens * 0.00000xxx` then sum per bin.
      </pattern>
      <pattern name="Per-tenant safe aggregation" location="(canonical KQL — author this task)">
        Where `tenantId` is a dimension, prefer aggregation across tenants in
        shared dashboards (Spaarke Dev). If per-tenant drill-down is desired,
        use Azure Workbook parameter binding rather than hardcoded `tenantId`
        filters. R5 task 042 ships shared-aggregation dashboards only; per-tenant
        drill-down is R6 backlog.
      </pattern>
    </patterns>
  </knowledge>

  <context>
    <background>
      R5 ships chat-driven Summarize-for-Chat across two invocation paths
      (agent-tool + direct endpoint). Task 008 instrumented both paths with a
      single coherent OpenTelemetry meter (`Sprk.Bff.Api.R5Summarize`) emitting
      `r5.summarize.invocation` (Counter) + four Histograms + a session-files
      index-size Histogram. The schema was deliberately treated as a
      public-API surface from task 008's commit forward — precisely so this
      dashboard task can write stable Kusto queries against it.

      This task is the LAST step in turning instrumentation into operational
      value. Without it, task 008's events sit in App Insights but are not
      surfaced for the four observability questions plan.md D3-03 calls out:
      invocation counts + path mix; index size; cost-per-session; SSE event-rate
      / latency. Spec NFR-06 (cost control) explicitly depends on the cost
      panel; spec NFR-02 (cleanup cadence tuning) depends on the index-size
      panel.

      Parallel-safe with task 041 (Get Started welcome card) because the
      surfaces don't overlap — 041 touches frontend, 042 touches dashboard
      infrastructure / portal artifacts.
    </background>
    <dependencies>
      <dependency task="008" status="prerequisite">
        Task 008 emits the events these dashboards consume. The locked schema
        in `notes/task-008-telemetry-evidence.md` is the binding contract.
      </dependency>
      <dependency task="phase-2" status="prerequisite">
        Phase 2 tasks 012/014/015 INVOKE `R5SummarizeTelemetry.RecordSummarizeInvocation(...)`
        + task 007's cleanup job INVOKES `RecordSessionFilesIndexSize(...)`.
        Without Phase 2 traffic, dashboards have no data to display. (Task can
        seed data via synthetic invocations if Spaarke Dev hasn't accumulated
        live traffic yet — see Step 7.)
      </dependency>
    </dependencies>
    <related-work>
      <item>`infrastructure/bicep/modules/dashboard.bicep` — existing SDAP AI
        Monitoring Dashboard. R5 dashboards EXTEND this precedent (additive
        tiles or a sibling module). Same `Microsoft.Portal/dashboards@2020-09-01-preview`
        resource type.</item>
      <item>Task 041 (D3-02 Get Started welcome card) — parallel-safe with this
        task; touches frontend SpaarkeAi shell + GetStartedCardsWidget catalog.
        No surface overlap; both can be dispatched in P3-2 wave.</item>
      <item>Task 043 (D3-04 operator-led end-to-end testing) — consumes these
        dashboards as part of the discoverability + correctness pass. Dashboard
        availability is implicitly a prerequisite for 043.</item>
      <item>Task 044 (D3-05 lessons-learned + R6 backlog) — captures any
        dashboard pattern improvements + per-tenant drill-down deferral as R6
        backlog items.</item>
    </related-work>
  </context>

  <steps>
    <step order="0" name="Context Check + RIGOR LEVEL declaration">
      Check context usage. If &gt; 70%, run `context-handoff` and request
      `/compact`. Declare:

      ```
      🔒 RIGOR LEVEL: FULL
      📋 REASON: Infrastructure / observability change consuming locked
        downstream-contract telemetry schema from task 008. Tags include
        `dashboards` + `telemetry` + `observability` per CLAUDE.md §8
        decision tree (FULL applies to BFF-adjacent infra changes that
        load-bear on operational decisions — spec NFR-02 cadence tuning +
        NFR-06 cost control both depend on these panels).
      📖 PROTOCOL STEPS TO EXECUTE: 0 (this) → 1 review → 2 gather →
        3 plan + placement decision → 4 author panel queries →
        5 author dashboard artifact (Bicep OR portal) → 6 deploy →
        7 verify against Spaarke Dev live data → 8 publish-size confirmation
        → 9 acceptance walkthrough → 9.5 quality gates → 10 document + complete
      Proceeding with Step 0...
      ```
    </step>
    <step order="1" name="Review Progress">
      Read `tasks/TASK-INDEX.md` and confirm task 042 status is 🔲, wave is
      P3-2, parallel-safe = ✅ (with 041), dependencies = Phase 2 ✅ + task 008.
      Verify Phase 2 is ✅ in the index (all P2 tasks ✅) and task 008 is ✅
      with `notes/task-008-telemetry-evidence.md` populated. Read
      `current-task.md` to confirm 042 is the active task. Read project README
      for project status.
    </step>
    <step order="2" name="Gather Resources">
      Read every file in &lt;inputs&gt; and &lt;knowledge&gt;. Specifically extract:
      (a) the canonical event schema table from
      `notes/task-008-telemetry-evidence.md` (this is the binding contract);
      (b) the exact instrument names + dimension names from
      `src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Telemetry/R5SummarizeTelemetry.cs` to
      cross-check the schema table; (c) the `Microsoft.Portal/dashboards@
      2020-09-01-preview` resource pattern from
      `infrastructure/bicep/modules/dashboard.bicep` (parameter list,
      lenses/parts structure); (d) the Azure OpenAI token-pricing constants
      for the deployed model from `docs/architecture/auth-AI-azure-resources.md`
      or environment configuration so the cost-per-session derivation is
      grounded in real prices.
    </step>
    <step order="3" name="Plan + Placement Decision (Bicep vs portal-managed)">
      Make the IaC-vs-portal-managed decision EXPLICITLY:
      - **Prefer Bicep IaC** when the dashboard is stable, audit-friendly,
        + needs to survive tenant rebuilds. R5 dashboards qualify (stable
        schema from task 008; production-bound observability).
      - **Accept portal-managed** only if Bicep authoring cost is
        disproportionate to value (e.g., exploratory mid-stabilization).
        If chosen, export the dashboard JSON to
        `infrastructure/dashboards/r5-summarize-dashboard.json` so it is
        reproducible.

      Default decision: **Bicep IaC** (extend
      `infrastructure/bicep/modules/dashboard.bicep` with additive parts OR
      add sibling module `infrastructure/bicep/modules/r5-summarize-dashboard.bicep`
      using the same resource pattern). Document the decision + rationale in
      task notes.

      Lock the 4-panel layout BEFORE authoring:

      | Panel | Source instrument | Stratification | Visualization |
      |---|---|---|---|
      | 1. Invocations + path mix | `r5.summarize.invocation` Counter | `path` × `completion_status` | Stacked timechart (5m bins) |
      | 2. Session-files index size | `r5.session_files.index_size` Histogram | `phase` | Multi-series line (p50/p95 per phase) |
      | 3. Cost-per-session | `r5.summarize.total_tokens` Histogram × pricing constant | `path` | Timechart of summed cost_usd per bin |
      | 4. SSE event-rate + latency | `r5.summarize.latency_ms` Histogram + Counter rate | `path` | Dual chart: rate + p50/p95/p99 with 500ms threshold marker |
    </step>
    <step order="4" name="Author 4 KQL queries">
      Author the four panel queries as standalone KQL files under
      `infrastructure/dashboards/queries/` (one `.kql` per panel) — this
      enables review-in-isolation + portability. Each query:
      - Starts with `customMetrics | where timestamp &gt; ago(...)` scoped to
        a sensible default window (24h for invocations + cost; 7d for
        index-size trend);
      - Filters `where name == "&lt;instrument-name&gt;"` using the exact
        locked instrument names;
      - Extends `customDimensions.&lt;dim&gt;` into typed columns;
      - Aggregates per `bin(timestamp, ...)` plus stratification dimensions;
      - Renders via `render timechart` (Panel 1, 3, 4 rate) or
        `render columnchart` (Panel 2) or `render linechart` (Panel 4 latency);
      - Annotates with `// derived from task-008 locked schema — DO NOT rename
        dimensions without coordinated dashboard update` header comment.

      For Panel 3 (cost): embed the per-token pricing constant in an `extend`
      clause with a comment citing the source (Azure OpenAI pricing page /
      `auth-AI-azure-resources.md` reference). When prices change, the constant
      is updated in one place.

      For Panel 4 (latency): include a horizontal threshold marker at 500ms
      using the `render linechart with (ytitle="latency (ms)", ymin=0)` config
      OR a workbook-level threshold rule. Surface the SSE TTFB commitment
      visibly.
    </step>
    <step order="5" name="Author dashboard artifact (Bicep preferred)">
      Per Step 3 decision:
      - **Bicep path**: Add new tiles to
        `infrastructure/bicep/modules/dashboard.bicep` OR create sibling module
        `infrastructure/bicep/modules/r5-summarize-dashboard.bicep` using the
        same `Microsoft.Portal/dashboards@2020-09-01-preview` resource pattern.
        Each panel = one `lenses[0].parts[]` entry with `MonitorChartPart` (for
        Panel 1, 3, 4 rate) or `LogsDashboardPart` (for KQL-driven panels).
        Embed the Step-4 KQL queries inline (or reference them via
        deployment-time parameter). Position via `x`, `y`, `rowSpan`,
        `colSpan` for a 2×2 grid layout.
      - **Portal path** (fallback): Author each panel in the Azure Portal
        directly; export dashboard JSON to
        `infrastructure/dashboards/r5-summarize-dashboard.json`; commit the
        JSON + a `README.md` adjacent documenting how to re-import (Azure
        Portal → Dashboards → New → upload JSON).
    </step>
    <step order="6" name="Deploy to Spaarke Dev">
      Deploy the dashboard to Spaarke Dev:
      - **Bicep path**: Run `az deployment group create ...` targeting the
        Spaarke Dev resource group + the dashboard module. Use the
        `azure-deploy` skill if applicable. Verify the dashboard appears in
        Azure Portal → Dashboards.
      - **Portal path**: Import the JSON via Azure Portal → Dashboards → New
        → upload. Verify all 4 panels render.

      Capture: dashboard name, dashboard resource ID, Azure Portal URL for
      task notes.
    </step>
    <step order="7" name="Verify panels against Spaarke Dev live data">
      For EACH of the 4 panels, open the panel + confirm:
      1. The query executes without error;
      2. The query returns non-empty rows from Spaarke Dev App Insights
         (within the panel's time window);
      3. The visualization renders correctly;
      4. Stratification dimensions appear as expected (e.g., Panel 1 shows
         both `agent_tool` and `direct_endpoint` series; Panel 2 shows all
         three `phase` values when cleanup has run).

      IF a panel returns no data because Spaarke Dev hasn't yet generated
      traffic for that instrument (e.g., session-files cleanup hasn't fired
      yet, OR no invocations have happened since dashboards-deployment-time):
      seed data by triggering synthetic invocations:
      - Manually invoke `/summarize` against a test session in Spaarke Dev
        (covers Panel 1, 3, 4);
      - Manually trigger task 007's cleanup job (or wait for the next 6h
        scheduled run) to emit `phase = "post_cleanup"` measurements (covers
        Panel 2);
      - Document the seed mechanism in task notes so re-verification is
        repeatable.

      Capture per-panel screenshot reference + sample data row count in task
      notes.
    </step>
    <step order="8" name="Publish-size confirmation (R5 §3.6)">
      No BFF code change in this task — verify by inspecting changed files:
      - Bicep path: changes are in `infrastructure/bicep/modules/*` +
        `infrastructure/dashboards/queries/*` only; ZERO files in
        `src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/`.
      - Portal path: changes are in `infrastructure/dashboards/*` only;
        ZERO files in `src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/`.

      Record explicitly in task notes: "BFF publish-size delta = 0 MB
      (no BFF binary change; verified by changed-file inspection)." No
      `dotnet publish` measurement required per R5 §3.6 (verification is
      "confirm delta = 0 MB by inspection" when no BFF code is changed).

      Also confirm no new packages → no CVE scan required (no NuGet change).
    </step>
    <step order="9" name="Verify Acceptance Criteria">
      Walk through every &lt;acceptance-criterion&gt; below and confirm each is
      testable + passing. Record evidence per criterion (panel screenshot
      reference, query row count, Spaarke Dev Portal URL, BFF publish-size
      = 0 MB inspection note, placement decision rationale) in task notes.
    </step>
    <step order="9.5" name="Quality Gates (FULL rigor)">
      Run `code-review` skill against the new + modified artifacts:
      - `infrastructure/bicep/modules/dashboard.bicep` (modified — additive
        tiles) OR `infrastructure/bicep/modules/r5-summarize-dashboard.bicep`
        (NEW) OR `infrastructure/dashboards/r5-summarize-dashboard.json`
        (NEW portal export, if portal path chosen);
      - `infrastructure/dashboards/queries/*.kql` (NEW — 4 KQL files);
      - `infrastructure/dashboards/README.md` (NEW if portal path; documents
        re-import).

      Run `adr-check` skill against the same files. Verify:
      - ADR-014 — tenant isolation: queries aggregate safely across tenants in
        shared Spaarke Dev dashboards; no per-tenant identifier leakage. ✅
      - ADR-015 — no PII / customer content in queries; only locked enum
        dimensions + counts + durations + tenantId. ✅
      - ADR-018 — no new feature flags introduced. ✅
      - ADR-029 — BFF publish hygiene: zero BFF code change; delta = 0 MB
        confirmed by inspection. ✅
      - ADR-030 — no PaneEventBus changes (out of scope; pure observability). ✅

      Both gates MUST pass before task complete.
    </step>
